Swapnil Tripathi

PhD Researcher · Electrical & Computer Engineering · University of California, Santa Cruz

I am a first-year PhD student at UCSC working on hybrid switched-capacitor DC-DC converters for high-density power delivery. I completed my M.S. from IIT Madras where I worked on multilevel inverter topologies, capacitor voltage balancing, and motor drives. My research interests span power electronics hardware, embedded control, and high-frequency converter design.

Key Projects

Hybrid Switched-Capacitor DC-DC Converter

2025–Present
PhD Research · University of California, Santa Cruz

Designing a 100W hybrid switched-capacitor converter for point-of-load applications targeting 48V→1V conversion at 1–2MHz switching frequency. Focus on high power density, low output impedance, and soft-charging operation.

Switched Capacitor Altium Designer Point-of-Load High Frequency
IISc Bengaluru campus · Power Electronics lab with Prof. Vishnu Mahadev Iyer

Grid-Tied Inverter Control

Feb–Jun 2025
Project Associate · IISc Bengaluru · Under Prof. Vishnu Mahadev Iyer

Implemented grid-tied control using a proportional-resonant (PR) controller with phase-locked loop (PLL) synchronization for a Nova converter topology. Developed real and reactive power control strategies for stable grid integration.

PR Controller PLL Nova Converter Grid-Tied

Multilevel Inverter Topologies & Motor Drives

2022–2025
M.S. Thesis Research · IIT Madras · Under Prof. Kamalesh Hatua

Developed capacitor voltage balancing PWM techniques for a 10kVA cascaded H-Bridge multilevel inverter driving a 1.5kW induction motor. Implemented NPV balancing, carrier-modified PWM, and field-oriented control on a TMS320F28377S DSP + Xilinx FPGA platform. Work resulted in two accepted IEEE papers (ECCE & IECON 2024).

Cascaded H-Bridge TMS320F28377S FPGA FOC NPV Balancing

Power Electronics Hardware — Formula Racing & Hyperloop

2022–2025
IIT Madras — Team Raftar Formula Racing & Team Avishkar Hyperloop

Team Raftar Formula Racing (IIT Madras × Daimler Trucks): Designed a 5kW 3-phase PMSM inverter for an electric formula car. Developed a 10kVA Si-IGBT gate driver with active Miller clamp, dead-time control, and short-circuit protection using KiCad.

Team Avishkar Hyperloop: Designed H-Bridge and 3-phase inverter hardware for electromagnetic levitation and linear traction systems. Competed at the European Hyperloop Week.

PMSM Inverter Si-IGBT Gate Driver KiCad Active Miller Clamp Hyperloop Formula Racing
Signal conditioning board · 3-phase inverter PCB · Team Raftar EV car · Avishkar Hyperloop pod
